		 	<span id="comment_score_64591643" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64591643); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>2</a>)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~AmiMoJo">AmiMoJo</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~AmiMoJo">( 196126 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64591643"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64591643"><p>Yep, and as a great example of that look at Ireland. It has two cables to mainland Britain, one of which is to the Irish grid. They are adding another to France, so that they can sell wind energy to France and buy nuclear from them.</p><p>If either cable goes down, Ireland won't go dark. They have one large flywheel already to help provide stability for their large amount of wind energy, and are looking at building another 5. They current one is in an old disused coal plant.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64591643">

